FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776250558
OL,3,CUK outlook darkens as IMF warns Iran
OL,4,Cwar could trigger global recession
OL,6,F"(This) has happened only four times
OL,7,Fsince 1980, with the latest two
OL,8,Foccasions corresponding to the global
OL,9,Ffinancial crisis and the COVID-19
OL,10,Fpandemic," the IMF notes in its report.
OL,12,FThe economic impact of the war will
OL,13,Fvary depending on whether countries
OL,14,Fare net importers or exporters of
OL,15,Fenergy. It is striking how resilient
OL,16,Fthe IMF expects the American economy
OL,17,Fto be.
OL,26,@nD@AOUnD@BpmnD@GpnrD@JO]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776250558
OL,3,CUK outlook darkens as IMF warns Iran
OL,4,Cwar could trigger global recession
OL,6,FThe UK's vulnerability lies in its
OL,7,Freliance on natural gas - to heat
OL,8,Fhomes and generate electricity - a
OL,9,Fvulnerability compounded by a
OL,10,Fcomparative lack of gas storage.
OL,12,FThe Ofgem energy price cap offers
OL,13,Fhouseholds some shelter from higher
OL,14,Fprices until the end of July, and the
OL,15,Ffull force of higher unit prices won't
OL,16,Fbe felt until temperatures drop in
OL,17,FOctober and people reach for the
OL,18,Fthermostat.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776250558
OL,3,CUK outlook darkens as IMF warns Iran
OL,4,Cwar could trigger global recession
OL,6,FThis also gives the government
OL,7,Fvaluable breathing space - to better
OL,8,Fassess the scale of the hit and work
OL,9,Fout how best to respond.
OL,11,FDuring the last energy price shock,
OL,12,Fthe previous government chose to
OL,13,Fsubsidise the bills of every household
OL,14,F- but did so with borrowed money (just
OL,15,Fover #100 billion) and at great cost.
OL,16,FThe UK now spends almost twice as much
OL,17,Fservicing its debts as it does on
OL,18,Fdefence.
OL,20,FThe government is under pressure to
OL,21,Fride to the rescue again.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,312,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31109
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F311A1776250558
OL,3,CUK outlook darkens as IMF warns Iran
OL,4,Cwar could trigger global recession
OL,6,FThe IMF warns of the dangers of
OL,7,Funiversal taxpayer support.
OL,8,F"Untargeted measures - price caps,
OL,9,Fsubsidies, and similar interventions -
OL,10,Fare popular. But they are frequently
OL,11,Fpoorly designed and costly," says
OL,12,FGourinchas.
OL,14,FThe government is already signalling
OL,15,Fthat further support will be
OL,16,Fforthcoming, but targeted at those
OL,17,Fjudged to need it most.
OL,26,@pD@AOUsD@\O]
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G9/12
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
